parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant valve can cause the engine to shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents and fatalities.
symptoms: The engine warning indicator and the "do not exceed 4
000 RPMS" warning indicator illuminate
the engine cuts off while driving
the check engine light and EPC light come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain and camshaft can cause the engine to fail, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents and fatalities.
symptoms: The check engine warning light is illuminated
the engine fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil plug can cause the engine to shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents and fatalities.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the check engine indicator illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of coolant can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even engine failure, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The coolant level is low
the coolant warning light is on
the vehicle is using excessive amounts of coolant
but no leaks are visible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension control arms can cause uneven braking, loss of control, and vibration, which can increase the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Thumping or clunking noise when braking
vibration on the steering wheel
the vehicle leans forward heavily when braking
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Failure of Control Arm Bushings
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of control arm bushings can cause uneven braking, loss of control, and vibration, which can increase the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Extreme vibration and erratic handling during braking
uneven tire wear
clunking or thumping noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coolant Leak into Engine Wire Harness and PCM
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The coolant leak into the engine wire harness and PCM can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop and become inoperable, leading to a high risk of accidents, especially in heavy traffic conditions. This issue can also cause the vehicle to be unable to shift into neutral, making it difficult to move the vehicle out of the way, and may result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops while in motion
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle is unable to restart
the vehicle is unable to engage neutral gear
coolant leak into the engine wire harness and PCM
shorted pins in the PCM.
